  "prompt": "Can you mix hair dye with your conditioner?",
  "response": "Yes, you can mix hair dye with conditioner, but there are some important considerations:\n\n1. Permanent or semi-permanent dye\n- Mixing hair dye with conditioner can slightly dilute the color intensity\n- It may result in a more subtle, softer color\n- Works best with semi-permanent dyes\n\n2. Benefits\n- Can help reduce damage to hair\n- May make the dye application smoother\n- Can help condition hair during coloring process\n\n3. Precautions\n- Use white/uncolored conditioner\n- Mix in small amounts\n- Follow hair dye instructions carefully\n- Do a strand test first to check color result\n- Not recommended for all hair dye types (check manufacturer's instructions)\n\n4. Best for\n- People with dry or damaged hair\n- Those wanting a less intense color\n- Semi-permanent hair dyes\n\n5. Not recommended for\n- Permanent hair dyes\n- Professional color treatments\n- When precise color matching is crucial\n\nAlways check the specific instructions on your hair dye product before mixing with conditioner.",
